content.description: In between Dumbo and the big water runoff/runnel.  Sit start under the roof and wonder straight up via large crimps and slots.  Make a big move coming out of the roof to slopey holds that eventually leads to good features.  Topout.
content.location: In between Dumbo and the big water

content.description: Sit start and trend right on giant iron crimp rails.  Move straight up to a left hand side-pull hold and topout straight up.
content.location: Right of Timothy Q and the big water runnel

content.description: Just left of Dumbo lies this amazing face line with good features. Stand-start low and make moves to the crimp line above. You will then encounter the biggest footlong jug you have ever seen. Move directly up to a sketchy topout. Locate the tiny pocket for a right hand at the lip, then locate good feet and mantle the slopey topout. Sketchy. Pads and spotters. Don’t fall.

The prominent arete line. Start underneath on jugs and make moves into the roof.  Reach up and around the arete to the left to locate the Giant “dumbo” ear jug.   From here stack high feet and bump out right to increasingly good slopers.  Topout straight up.  Careful not to dab on the tree! Sketchy. Pads and Spotters.
content.location: The prominent arete line. Dumbo Boulder

content.description: The beautiful big boulder downhill from the Passage Boulder. The lower roof has sandy, chossy rock but the uphill face and arete offer wonderful lines.
